<item>
            <title>[LU-12712] sanity-pfl tests triggering &#8220;not SEL magic on SEL file&#8221;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12712</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Looking at the console log for MDSs when running sanity-pfl, we are seeing messages like&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[13646.271068] Lustre: 21851:0:(lod_lov.c:1358:lod_parse_striping()) lustre-MDT0001-mdtlov: not SEL magic on SEL file [0x240014454:0x77a:0x0]: bd30bd0
[13646.274907] Lustre: 21851:0:(lod_lov.c:1358:lod_parse_striping()) lustre-MDT0001-mdtlov: not SEL magic on SEL file [0x240014454:0x77a:0x0]: bd30bd0
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are seeing this for sanity-pfl tests 19e, 20b, 20c and 20d and when cleaning up after sanity-pfl.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Examples of this message in the MDS (vm4 and vm5) console logs are at&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/fedacd8c-c944-11e9-90ad-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/fedacd8c-c944-11e9-90ad-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/b04ecaf6-c953-11e9-97d5-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/b04ecaf6-c953-11e9-97d5-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
